OL,3,CHow to save someone's life with a
OL,4,Cbleed kit
OL,6,FTrauma dressings are a highly
OL,7,Fabsorbent padded dressing that can be
OL,8,Fused to cover the wound, followed by
OL,9,Fsustained pressure to the area.
OL,11,FHaemostatic dressings
OL,13,FHaemostatic dressings accelerate blood
OL,14,Fclotting to control severe bleeding in
OL,15,Ftrauma situations, reducing blood
OL,16,Floss. These should be used at junction
OL,17,Fregions like the neck, groin and
OL,18,Farmpit.
